***That the Poet's spirits are high at the thought of the addressee,
and that a soaring bird singing at dawn is consistent with this, is
true enough. But, particularly with the Cloten quote to consider, it
doesn't come through to me that &quot;heaven's gate&quot; necessarily implies
&quot;high&quot; any more than it does &quot;the commencing of dawn,&quot; both being
