enough with his usual babbling and those naughty jokes and disgusting
puns--he ended up getting crazy drunk and smearing jam all over his
doublet. Then--can you believe his bad Fortune?--he stumbled over the
cat right into a punch bowl at the next table, and the punch splashed
right into the eyes of that fop Sir Wilbert Filbert and his buddy
Fantastico Nutt. Believe you me, he's a downright outcast--can't show
his face there for a year without getting laughed right out the door!
Lucky for him he has to be on the road back and forth to Stratford for
a couple of weeks!!!&quot;), the absence of stated or implied circumstances
concerning banishment, the lack of anything to suggest that his travel
is anything more than a wearisome personal task, and whatever else I
might be blithering about above, Bob's reading of the situation is as
likely as any.

